      <section eId="sec_426">
        <num>426</num>
        <heading>Issuance of summons</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_426__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>On the filing of a petition under this\narticle, the court may cause a copy of the petition and a summons to be\nissued, requiring the respondent to show cause why the order of support\nand other and further relief prayed for by the petition should not be\nmade.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_426__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The summons shall contain or have attached thereto a notice\nstating:</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_426__subsec_i">
          <num>(i)</num>
          <content>
            <p>that a respondent's failure to appear shall result in entry\nof an order of default; (ii) that the respondent must provide the court\nwith proof of his or her income and assets; (iii) that a temporary or\npermanent order of support will be made on the return date of the\nsummons; and (iv) that a respondent's failure to appear may result in\nthe suspension of his or her driving privileges; state professional,\noccupational and business licenses; and recreational licenses and\npermits.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
